menu "Kernel Configuration"

config KERNEL_PREEMPT_ENABLED
    bool "Enable preemptive scheduling"
    default y
    help
      When enabled, a higher-priority thread can preempt a lower-priority
      one at any preemption point (system call, timer tick, IPI).
      Disable only for cooperative scheduling.

config NUM_PRIORITIES
    int "Number of thread priority levels"
    default 32
    range 2 64
    help
      Total number of distinct priority levels (0 = lowest, N-1 = highest).
      Each level has its own run queue. A larger value increases RAM usage
      slightly but provides finer scheduling granularity.

config TIMESLICE_MS
    int "Time-slice duration in milliseconds (round-robin)"
    default 10
    range 1 1000
    depends on KERNEL_PREEMPT_ENABLED
    help
      For threads at the same priority, the scheduler performs round-robin
      with this time slice. Set to 0 to disable time-slicing.

config TICKLESS_IDLE
    bool "Enable tickless idle (dynamic tick)"
    default y
    help
      When the system is idle, suppresses periodic tick interrupts and
      programs the hardware timer to wake up only for the next scheduled
      event. Reduces power consumption significantly.

config SMP
    bool "Symmetric Multi-Processing (SMP) support"
    default n
    help
      Enable SMP support for multi-core processors (e.g., RP2350 dual-core
      Cortex-M33). Adds per-CPU data structures and IPI (inter-processor
      interrupt) for cross-core reschedule.

config SMP_NUM_CPUS
    int "Number of CPUs"
    default 2
    range 2 4
    depends on SMP
    help
      Number of CPU cores to use. Must match the actual hardware.

config STACK_CANARY
    bool "Enable stack overflow canary detection"
    default y
    help
      Places a magic value (canary) at the bottom of each thread stack.
      The kernel checks the canary on context switch; if corrupted, a
      fatal error is triggered. Small overhead in exchange for safety.

config TLS
    bool "Enable thread-local storage (TLS)"
    default y
    help
      Allocates a small per-thread data block (TLS) within each thread's
      stack region. Used by subsystems like logging for per-thread state.

config SCHED_DYNAMIC_PRIORITY
    bool "Enable dynamic priority switching"
    default y
    help
      Allows threads to change their own or another thread's priority at
      runtime with vibe_thread_set_priority(). Required for priority
      inheritance in mutexes.

config IDLE_STACK_SIZE
    int "Idle thread stack size in bytes"
    default 256
    range 128 2048
    help
      Stack size for the per-CPU idle thread.

config SYS_WORKQ_STACK_SIZE
    int "System work queue thread stack size in bytes"
    default 1024
    range 512 8192
    help
      Stack size for the system work queue worker thread.

config SYS_WORKQ_PRIORITY
    int "System work queue thread priority"
    default 30
    range 0 31
    help
      Priority of the system work queue worker thread.

endmenu
